    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-20T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-20T14:00:00-05:00" n="342"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d342">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.652/119: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-20T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 20, 1937—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>176. Your 481, November 19, noon.<note n="33" xml:id="d342fn33">Not
                        printed.</note> From Sayre. I suggest if you see no objection that you
                    inform the Italian Government that we are now at work on a reply but that if, as
                    seems likely, the new treaty is not signed by December 15 we hope to bridge the
                    interval before the new treaty comes into force by working out some arrangement
                    covering the generalizing of trade agreement rates to Italian products. Personal
                    letter follows giving further particulars.<note n="34" xml:id="d342fn34">See
                        letter of November 19, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> [Sayre.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
